      <section eId="sec_20_2_697">
        <num>20-2-697</num>
        <content>
          <p>(a.1)Any student shall have the right to request and receive, within three business days from the date of such request, a letter from his or her school administrator indicating that the student is enrolled full-time and has an attendance record in good standing for the current academic year.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1945, p. 343, § 9; Ga. L. 1969, p. 838, § 4; Ga. L. 1981, p. 829, § 1; Ga. L. 1984, p. 1266, § 5; Ga. L. 1989, p. 808, § 3; Ga. L. 1997, p. 760, § 5; Ga. L. 2000, p. 618, §§ 63, 94; Ga. L. 2004, p. 107, § 11A; Ga. L. 2015, p. 60, § 3-4/SB 100.)</p>
          <p>The 2015 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2015, in subsection (a), substituted "verification of enrollment by the Department of Driver Services" for "verification of attendance by the Department of Public Safety" near the end of the fifth sentence. See editor's note for applicability.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
